Introduction

M.I.B (Korean: 엠아이비; Japanese: Mアイビー; Most Incredible Busters) was a four-member Korean hip-hop group formed by Jungle Entertainment. The group consisted of members 5Zic, Kangnam, Young Cream, and Sims.

They made their official debut on October 25th 2011 with the self-titled and self-produced album "Most Incredible Busters". Before debuting, all 4 members released solo songs to showcase their individual skills.

The group's last release was their second album "The Maginot Line" which was released in 2014 with the title track "Chisa Bounce". They later went on hiatus until their eventual disbandment on January 4th, 2017.
